<BLOCK1><TI><UNDER>AMENDED</UNDER> NOTICE OF APPEAL <EM>FORM 7 (RULE 11(A))</EM></TI>
<P>Take notice that RED BRANCH INVESTMENTS LIMITED and GERALD WRIGHT, hereby appeal to the Court of Appeal for British Columbia from the order of The Honourable Mr. Justice Wong of the Supreme Court of British Columbia pronounced the 27th day of November, 2015 at Vancouver, British Columbia <UNDER>and from the order of The Honourable Mr. Justice Wong of the Supreme Court of British Columbia pronounced on the 9<SUP>th</SUP> day of February, 2016, at Vancouver, British Columbia.</UNDER></P>
<P>1. The appeal is from a:
<P1>[&check;] Trial Judgment</P1>
<P1>&square; Summary Trial Judgment</P1>
<P1>&square; Order of a Statutory Body</P1>
<P1>&square; Chambers Judgment</P1></P>
<P>2. If the appeal is from an appeal under Rule 18-3 or 23-6(8) of the <EM>Supreme Court Civil Rules</EM> or Rule 18-3 or 22-7(8) of the <EM>Supreme Court Family Rules</EM>, name the maker of the original decision, direction or order.</P>
<P>3. Please identify which of the following is involved in the appeal:
<P1>&square; Constitutional/Administrative</P1>
<P1>&square; Civil Procedure</P1>
<P1>[&check;] Commercial</P1>
<P1>Family&mdash;</P1>
<P1>&square; <EM>Divorce</EM></P1>
<P1>&square; <EM>Family Law Act</EM></P1>
<P1>&square; <EM>Corollary Relief in a Divorce Proceeding</EM></P1>
<P1>&square; <EM>Other Family</EM></P1>
<P1>&square; Motor Vehicle Accidents</P1>
<P1>&square; Municipal Law</P1>
<P1>&square; Real Property</P1>
<P1>&square; Torts</P1>
<P1>&square; Equity</P1>
<P1>&square; Wills and Estates</P1></P>
<P>(The Divorce Registry will, as applicable, be notified by the Court of Appeal Registry on filing if the appeal involves divorce, corollary relief in divorce proceeding or matters under the <EM>Family Law Act</EM>.)</P>
<P>And further take notice that the Court of Appeal will be moved at the hearing of this appeal for an order that:
<P1>1. the order of the Honourable Mr. Justice Wong, pronounced November 27, 2015, be set aside;</P1>
<P1>2. the appeal be allowed;</P1>
<P1>3. the plaintiff's (respondent's) claim, as set out in his notice of civil claim, be dismissed;</P1>
<P1>4. in the alternative, that there be a new trial or that the matter be submitted to the Supreme Court for reconsideration;</P1>
<P1><UNDER>5. in the further alternative, that the order of the Honourable Mr. Justice Wong, pronounced February 9, 2016, be set aside;</UNDER></P1>
<P1>6. costs of this appeal, and in the court below.</P1></P>
<P>The trial/hearing of this proceeding occupied 16 days.</P>
<P>DATED at Vancouver, British Columbia, this <STRIKE>24th day of December, 2015</STRIKE> <UNDER>10<SUP>th</SUP> day of March, 2016</UNDER>.</P>
