<?TBLROW 1>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">1974&mdash;late June 2011</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2">The defendant, Gerald Wright, and the plaintiff, David Long, are friends.</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 2>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">&newline;</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2"></TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 3>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">June, 1992</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2">Crew Capital Corporation, the shareholders of which are Gerald Wright, John Darch, and Bob Anderson, acquires a royalty in a prospective potash mine in the province of Udon Thani, Thailand.</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 4>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">&newline;</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2"></TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 5>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">November, 1997</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2">The shareholders of Crew Capital Corporation agree that the royalty should be sold in equal parts to the three respective shareholders of the company, so that the corporation can be struck.</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 6>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">&newline;</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2"></TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 7>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">February, 1999</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2">The Royalty Agreement is executed with an effective date of November 28, 1997, transferring the royalty in equal parts from Crew Capital Corporation to Alice Anderson, 540438 B.C. Ltd. (a company controlled by John Darch), and David Long. Gerald Wright funds the purchase of the royalty interest by David Long, in the amount of $13,333.</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 8>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">&newline;</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2"></TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 9>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">First week of July, 2009</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2">Gerald Wright causes David Long to execute an agreement transferring the one third royalty interest to an entity to be filled in later by Mr. Wright on the agreement. The agreement is held by Mr. Wright in his safe at his home in West Vancouver. The agreement is referred to as the &ldquo;Blank Agreement&rdquo; at the trial.</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 10>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">&newline;</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2"></TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 11>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">November, 2006</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2">John Darch and Gerald Wright, as agent for David Long because the royalty interest is still held in his name, retain Fasken Martineau DuMoulin LLP, to provide them with advice in relation to a potential transfer of the right to develop the mine from Asia Pacific Resources to Italian-Thai.</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 12>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">&newline;</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2"></TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 13>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">November 10, 2009</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2">Red Branch Investments Limited is incorporated in Hong Kong as a Wright family holding company. The directors are Gerald Wright and his wife Gail Wright, and the shareholders are Gerald Wright, Gail Wright, and their children. Some of the Wright family assets are vended into the company.</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 14>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">&newline;</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2"></TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 15>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">In 2009 or 2010</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2">The Red Branch Agreement is executed, transferring the one third royalty interest from David Long to Red Branch. The plaintiff takes the position that the agreement was executed in June 2010 (which appears to have been accepted by the trial judge) and the defendants take the position that it was executed in December 2009. The reference date of the Agreement is September 1, 2009.</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 16>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">&newline;</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2"></TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 17>
