<BLOCK1><TI TOCID="I">CHRONOLOGY OF DATES RELEVANT TO THE APPEAL</TI>
<P>
<TABLE>
<SGMLTBL>
<TBLBODY TBLWD="600">
<TBLCDEFS COLSEP="VDOT" HALIGN="LEFT" CHARPOS="75%" TOPSEP="HDOT">
<TBLCDEF COLWD="20" TBLUNITS="PERCENT">
<TBLCDEF COLWD="80" TBLUNITS="PERCENT">
</TBLCDEFS>
<TBLROWS ROWSEP="HDOT" VALIGN="TOP" LEFTSEP="VDOT">
<?TBLROW 1>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">1974</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2">The defendant, Gerald Wright (&ldquo;<BOLD>Wright</BOLD>&rdquo;) and the plaintiff, David Long (&ldquo;<BOLD>Long</BOLD>), meet and become close friends.</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 2>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">&newline;</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2"></TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 3>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">August 1996</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2">Wright and Long incorporate two companies in Ireland in which they are equal shareholders, directors and officers.</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 4>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">&newline;</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2"></TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 5>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">Nov. 6, 1997</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2">Shareholders of Crew Capital Corp. (&ldquo;<BOLD>Crew</BOLD>&rdquo;) meet and agree that the royalty held by Crew in a prospective potash mine in Thailand (the &ldquo;<BOLD>Royalty</BOLD>&rdquo;) should be sold and that the company be wound up. The three shareholders of Crew are Wright, John Darch (&ldquo;<BOLD>Darch</BOLD>&rdquo;) and Bob Anderson (collectively, the &ldquo;<BOLD>Shareholders</BOLD>&rdquo;). Even though the sale is not affected, Crew reports it to CRA in the 1997 tax year.</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 6>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">&newline;</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2"></TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 7>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">Nov. 1997</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2">The date that Gail Wright (&ldquo;<BOLD>Mrs. Wright</BOLD>&rdquo;) says she placed the agreement by which Crew sold the Royalty to the Shareholders (the &ldquo;<BOLD>Royalty Agreement</BOLD>&rdquo;) into the safe in their West Vancouver home.</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 8>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">&newline;</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2"></TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 9>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">Dec. 9, 1997</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2">The date Wright and Mrs. Wright insist Long signed a promissory note in favour of Crew for the purchase of the Royalty, in the amount of $13,333 (the &ldquo;<BOLD>Promissory Note</BOLD>&rdquo;).</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 10>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">&newline;</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2"></TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 11>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">Apr. 1998</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2">Construction begins on the Dublin Sports Caf&ea; Ltd. dba Shooters, in Dublin (the &ldquo;<BOLD>Pub</BOLD>&rdquo;), which is owned equally by Wright and Long.</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 12>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">&newline;</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2"></TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 13>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">Oct. 22, 1998</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2">The Pub opens, but never turns a profit, and is ultimately put into liquidation on October 17, 2003.</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 14>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">&newline;</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2"></TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 15>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">Nov. 1998</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2">Bob Anderson, one of the three Crew Shareholders, dies.</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 16>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">&newline;</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2"></TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 17>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">Feb. 16, 1999</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2">An opinion is provided by the accounting firm Blair Crosson Voyer (the &ldquo;<BOLD>Opinion</BOLD>&rdquo;) on how to deal with various tax issues related to the reported sale of the Royalty to the Shareholders.</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 18>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">&newline;</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2"></TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 19>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">Feb. 1999</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2">The date that the Royalty Agreement was found by the trial judge to have been entered into. Alice Anderson, the wife of Bob Anderson, is named in the Royalty Agreement in his place even though the effective date of this agreement is November 28, 1997.</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 20>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">&newline;</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2"></TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 21>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1"></TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2">When Long says he signed the Promissory Note, and which Darch says 540438 BC Ltd. entered into on his behalf, and Alice Anderson provided similar promissory notes for Crew, also in the amount of $13,333 each, but all dated November 28, 1997.</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 22>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">&newline;</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2"></TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 23>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">Feb. 19, 1999</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2">Wright issues a personal cheque from his own account to his company Cypress Consulting Services Inc. (&ldquo;<BOLD>Cypress</BOLD>&rdquo;) in the amount of $15,000, to wire funds to Long. Cypress then wires $15,073.30 to Long the same day.</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 24>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">&newline;</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2"></TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 25>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">Feb. 24, 1999</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2">George Brazier, counsel for Crew, sent a letter enclosing the final form of the Royalty Agreement and promissory notes to be executed by the Shareholders, including Alice Anderson in place of Bob Anderson.</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 26>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">&newline;</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2"></TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 27>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">Feb. 26, 1999</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2">Long wires $14,310 to Crew as payment for the Royalty.</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 28>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">&newline;</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2"></TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 29>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">Apr/May 1999</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2">The date that Long says Wright visits him in Belfast, with his Thai mistress, Ms. Suchada Sanksuwan. Long says that Wright had him sign a blank transfer agreement for the Royalty (the &ldquo;<BOLD>Blank Transfer Agreement</BOLD>&rdquo;) during this visit.</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 30>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">&newline;</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2"></TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 31>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">Jul. 1999</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2">The date that Wright claims that Long signed the Blank Transfer Agreement.</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 32>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">&newline;</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2"></TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 33>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">Spring 2006</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2">The owner of the prospective mine, Asia Pacific Resources Ltd. (&ldquo;<BOLD>Asia Pacific</BOLD>&rdquo;), is bought out by Italia Thai, prompting Darch to believe that the Royalty had significantly more value and needed to be protected. As a result, Darch contacts Wright and they agree that counsel should be retained to insure Italia Thai will honour the Royalty.</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 34>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">&newline;</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2"></TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 35>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">Apr. 25, 2006</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2">Long signs a letter appointing Wright as his agent to act on his behalf in relation to matters related to the Royalty. Wright writes to David Anderson confirming that he acts as agent for Long in relation to the Royalty.</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 36>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">&newline;</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2"></TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 37>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">Jun. 28, 2006</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2">Retainer letter is sent to Darch and Long by the law firm of Fasken Martineau. Long is named as their client and signs the retainer letter with Wright acting as his agent.</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 38>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">&newline;</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2"></TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 39>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">Aug. 20, 2006</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2">Tax advice is received which provides that Long would be subject to withholding tax on the Royalty.</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 40>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">&newline;</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2"></TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 41>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">Nov. 9, 2006</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2">Wright advises Fasken Martineau that Long will be assigning his portion of the Royalty to a private (European) holding company.</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 42>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">&newline;</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2"></TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 43>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">Nov. 2009</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2">The date Wright claims that Long signed an agreement transferring the Royalty to the defendant, Red Branch Investments Ltd. (&ldquo;<BOLD>Red Branch</BOLD>&rdquo;), effective September 1, 2009 (the &ldquo;<BOLD>Red Branch Transfer Agreement</BOLD>&rdquo;).</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 44>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">&newline;</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2"></TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 45>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">Nov. 10, 2009</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2">Red Branch is incorporated in Hong Kong.</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 46>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">&newline;</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2"></TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
<?TBLROW 47>
<TBLROW>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="1">Nov. 24, 2009</TBLCELL>
<TBLCELL COLSTART="2">Wright informs Fasken Martineau that Long will be assigning his Royalty interest to a private (Hong Kong) company.</TBLCELL>
</TBLROW>
