<BLOCK1><TI TOCID="I">AFFIDAVIT</TI>
<P>I, Gabeba Slamang, paralegal, c/o 1100 - 570 Granville Street, Vancouver, B.C., AFFIRM THAT:</P>
<P>1. I am a paralegal with Fraser Litigation Group, lawyers for the respondent/plaintiff in this appeal and, as such, I have personal knowledge of the facts and matters herein deposed to save and except where the same are stated to be based on information and belief and where so stated I verily believe the same to be true.</P>
<P>2. I am advised by Ms. Michelle Tribe, partner of Fraser Litigation Group, and verily believe, that the within appeal is an appeal of an order of Mr. Justice Wong granting the relief sought by the plaintiff at trial, and an order of Mr. Justice Wong awarding the plaintiff special costs of the trial.</P>
<P>3. Attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;A&rdquo;</BOLD> is a true copy of the reasons for judgment of Mr. Justice Wong, issued November 27, 2015.</P>
<P>4. Attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;B&rdquo;</BOLD> is a true copy of the Order After Trial of Mr. Justice Wong, dated November 27, 2015 and entered March 30, 2016.</P>
<P>5. Attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;C&rdquo;</BOLD> is a true copy of the oral reasons for judgment of Mr. Justice Wong regarding the respondent's application for special costs, issued February 9, 2016.</P>
<P>6. Attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;D&rdquo;</BOLD> is a true copy of the Order After Application regarding special costs, dated February 9, 2016 and entered March 30, 2016.</P>
<P>7. Attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;E&rdquo;</BOLD> is a true copy of the appellants' notice of appeal, filed December 24, 2015.</P>
<P>8. Attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;F&rdquo;</BOLD> is a true copy of the respondent's notice of appearance, filed December 29, 2015.</P>
<P>9. Based upon my review of the pleadings and correspondence between the parties, I can confirm that:
<P1>(a) on February 11, 2016, Ms. Tribe sent a letter to Owais Ahmed, counsel for the appellants, preemptively advising that the respondent would not consent to a waiver or extension of the time periods set out in the <EM>Court of Appeal Rules</EM>, a true copy of which letter is attached hereto as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;G&rdquo;</BOLD>;</P1>
<P1>(b) on February 22, 2016, Mr. Ahmed sent a letter to Ms. Tribe enclosing the appeal record and transcripts filed February 22, 2016, a true copy of which letter without enclosures is attached hereto as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;H&rdquo;;</BOLD></P1>
<P1>(c) on March 10, 2016, Mr. Ahmed sent a letter to Ms. Tribe enclosing a copy of the filed amended notice of appeal, a copy of which is attached hereto as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;I&rdquo;.</BOLD> I am advised by Ms. Tribe, and verily believe, that, although dated March 10, 2016, the letter was not delivered to Ms. Tribe until March 11, 2016;</P1>
<P1>(d) on March 16, 2016, Mr. Ahmed sent a letter to Ms. Tribe requesting that the respondent consent to the filing of a Joint Appeal Book, a true copy of which letter is attached hereto as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;J&rdquo;</BOLD>;</P1>
<P1>(e) on March 21, 2016, Ms. Tribe sent an email to Mr. Ahmed advising that it would be prudent for the parties to file separate appeal books, a true copy of which email is attached hereto as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;K&rdquo;.</BOLD> I am advised by Ms. Tribe and verily believe that she sent this email from her cellular telephone and that the email contains two autocorrect errors in which the word &ldquo;farm&rdquo; ought to have read &ldquo;factum&rdquo; and the word &ldquo;vault&rdquo; ought to have read &ldquo;vastly&rdquo;;</P1>
<P1>(f) on March 22, 2016, Mr. Ahmed sent a letter to Ms. Tribe advising that he had been operating under the mistaken assumption that the respondent would consent to a joint appeal book and requesting the respondent's consent to a short extension for the filing of the appellants' materials. A true copy of this letter is attached hereto as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;L&rdquo;</BOLD>;</P1>
<P1>(g) on March 23, 2016, a letter was sent to Mr. Ahmed under Ms. Tribe's name advising that the respondent had, on February 11, 2016, given the appellant notice that no extensions of time would be consented to by the respondent and that the respondent had not agreed to file a joint appeal book. A true copy of this letter is attached hereto as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;M&rdquo;</BOLD>;</P1>
<P1>(h) on April 4, 2016, Mr. Ahmed sent a letter to Ms. Tribe advising that the appellants would bring an application for an extension of time and a stay of execution, and requesting Ms. Tribe's availability. A true copy of this letter is attached hereto as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;N&rdquo;</BOLD>;</P1>
<P1>(i) on April 4, 2016, Ms. Tribe sent a letter to Mr. Ahmed advising of her availability for the applications and requesting the appellants' application materials within the time set out in the <EM>Court of Appeal Rules</EM>. A true copy of this letter is attached hereto as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;O&rdquo;</BOLD>;</P1>
<P1>(j) on September 12, 2016, Ms. Tribe sent a letter to Mr. Ahmed requesting his availability for an application in relation to the within matter, a true copy of which letter is attached hereto as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;P&rdquo;</BOLD>; and</P1>
<P1>(k) on September 13, 2016, Mr. Ahmed sent a letter to Ms. Tribe advising of his availability for the proposed application, a true copy of which letter is attached hereto as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;Q&rdquo;.</BOLD></P1></P>
<P>10. I am advised by Ms. Tribe and verily believe that, to date, Ms. Tribe has not received the appellants' application materials, factum, or appeal book.</P>
