<BLOCK1><TI>AFFIDAVIT</TI>
<P>I, Gerald D. Wright, Businessman, of [location omitted] [location omitted] MAKE OATH AND SAY AS FOLLOWS:</P>
<P>1. I am one of the appellants in this matter and am an officer and director of the other appellant Red Branch Investments Limited (<BOLD>&ldquo;Red Branch&rdquo;</BOLD>), and as such I have personal knowledge of the matters and facts herein deposed to save and except where the same are stated to be made upon information and belief and as to the latter I verily believe them to be true.</P>
<P>2. I obtained a Bachelor of Science in engineering from Queen's University in Belfast, Northern Ireland in 1974, and obtained a Doctor of Philosophy in engineering from the same university in 1978.</P>
<P>3. I immigrated to Canada in 1979 and have worked in the mineral resource industry since that time.</P>
<P>4. I have reviewed Affidavit #1 of John Darch, sworn December 14, 20 17, and make this affidavit in response. He has spent a significant amount of time restating his evidence from the trial in his affidavit, including his statement that I told him that it was my intention to share the royalty in question with Mr. David P. Long. I responded to his evidence at the trial during my own testimony, and I therefore decline to repeat my evidence again. Simply put, I do not agree that I ever told him anything of the sort.</P>
<P>5. However, he has made some serious new assertions against me in his affidavit, to which I feel compelled to respond. At paragraph 12 of his affidavit, Mr. Darch states that his wife was frightened by me and what I might do in revenge for Mr. Darch testifying. I have never physically threatened Mr. Darch or any other members of his family, and I have no idea what the basis of that statement is. I do not believe that I have ever given Mr. Darch or any member of his family any reason to be &ldquo;frightened&rdquo;.</P>
<P>6. Moreover, I never attempted to even speak to Mr. Darch once it became clear that he was going to testify at the trial, let alone try and dissuade him from doing so.</P>
<P>7. It is the case that Mr. Darch and I were involved in litigation against one another relating to the dissolution of our long-term business dealings. Both sides made serious allegations against one another in that litigation, and the litigation was ha rd fought and pursued vigorously by both parties. However, the dispute was eventually resolved by way of a settlement and the matter never even went to trial. Mr. Darch and I have not been involved in any other litigation against one another.</P>
<P>8. Mr. Darch nonetheless asserts at paragraph 23 of his affidavit that in &ldquo;his experience and opinion, in litigation, [I] had the ability to be manipulative and extremely aggressive&rdquo;. Despite the seriousness of the allegation that I have been &ldquo;manipulative&rdquo; in litigation with him in the past, Mr. Darch has again failed to provide any concrete details to explain exactly what his &ldquo;experience and opinion&rdquo; is based on. It is therefore impossible for me to respond, other than to say that his accusation is not true and I disagree with his characterization of me.</P>
<P>
